The various types of damage a weapon or monster can do is placed into
a bitfield and as such may be combined and/or masked with the | and &
bitwise operators.

Please see the armour documentation for specifics about adding weaknesses
and resistances to your armour, and the weapon documentation for
specifics about adding damage types to your weapons.  This file only
lists the types of damage and the bitfield names for each type.

To use the following types, you must #include <types.h> in your file.

** damage types **

WEAPON_PIERCE    Piercing damage (darts, spears, needles)
WEAPON_SLASH     Slashing damage (razors, swords)
WEAPON_BLUNT     Blunt damage (clubs, maces, trashcans)
WEAPON_CLEAVE    Cleaving damage (axes, halberds)
WEAPON_DAM_MASK  WEAPON_PIERCE|WEAPON_SLASH|WEAPON_BLUNT|WEAPON_CLEAVE
DAM_SILVER       Silver objects (silver arrows, silver daggers)
DAM_MAGIC        Generic magic
DAM_GOOD         "Good" damage (aura bolt, holy fire, holy water, angels)
DAM_EVIL         "Evil" damage (demons, vampires)
DAM_CHAOS        Disruptive damage (disintegration, large-scale crushing)
DAM_LAW          "lawful" damage
DAM_ALIGN        DAM_GOOD|DAM_EVIL|DAM_LAW|DAM_CHAOS
DAM_FIRE         Heat and flame damage (fire spells, solar weapons)
DAM_COLD         Ice and freezing damage (hail, ice spells)
DAM_LIGHTNING    Electrical damage (lightning, electric eels)
ELEMENT_DAM_MASK DAM_LIGHTNING|DAM_COLD|DAM_FIRE|DAM_WATER
DAM_POISON       Poisonous damage (snakes, poisonous plants, swamps)
DAM_DISEASE      Health-degrading damage (zombies, mummies)
DAM_LIVING       DAM_POISON|DAM_DISEASE
DAM_SOUND        Sound damage (banshee, bards)
DAM_ACID         Acid damage (black dragons)
DAM_ASTRAL       Etherial and other-worldly (ghosts, shadows)
DAM_PSIONIC      Mental damage (mind sting)
DAM_WATER        Liquid damage (drowning)
DAM_AP           Armor-piercing damage (ultra-sharp weapons).
DAM_LIGHT        Light damage (sunray)
ALL_DAM_TYPES    All of the previous types.

